<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIE TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Monsieur Hire (Bravo Monday at 6 p.m.) is the underrated 1989 film that stars 
Michel Blanc as a mysterious bachelor-voyeur and Sandrine Bonnaire as the 
sensual young woman upon whom he preys. They are luminous enough to warrant a 
watch, but this film is not in the same league with the Claude Chabrol films it 
recalls. 
</P>
