<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEACH BLANKET BOOKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By E.W. Alexander 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New this week:  
</P>
<P>
 THE GIFT by Danielle Steel (Delacorte: $15). There are two surprises here; a 
simultaneous Spanish translation ("El Regalo," issued in paperback, $9.95) and 
a more Nineties theme.The venerable love triangle remains at the heart; but it 
involves the Whittakers, their son Tommy and his pregnant friend Maribeth. 
(Also available on audio cassette.) 
</P>
<P>
 THE FLOATING CITY by Eric Lustbader (Pocket: $22). A sequel to "The Kaisho" 
and clearly a set-up for the next book. Prepare yourself for our hero's 
mysterious "tanjian eye" and his friend's prosthetic hand (with retractable 
claws) in Lustbader's latest Asian thriller. (Also available on audio 
cassette.) 
</P>
<P>
 INTENT TO HARM by Stan Washburn (Pocket: $22). Detailed police procedural 
about a serial killer terrorizing a college town hones in on the painstaking 
work it sometimes takes for the police to get their man -- sometimes only to 
watch him slip away. It takes one to know one; the author was a former Berkeley 
Police reservist. E.W. Alexander 
</P>
