<TEXT>
<P>
 AMERICAN CIVIL WAR REPORTS AS RECORDED IN HARPER'S WEEKLY edited by Sidney 
Rudeau (Historical Briefs Inc., Box 629, 260 Madalyn Ave., Verplanck, N.Y. 
10596: $24.95; 224 pp., paperback original). These accounts from "A Journal of 
Civilization" give the reader a sense of the War as contemporary readers knew 
it. In addition to news stories and dispatches, the reproduced magazine pages 
include commentaries, cartoons and advertisements (a silver "Army" watch on a 
vest chain: $7). The dramatic woodcuts of battles, generals, congressmen, 
private soldiers and escaped slaves provide a vivid pictorial compliment to the 
many written accounts of the Civil War. 
