<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW RELEASES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON HECKMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AL JARREAU 
</P>
<P>
 "Tenderly" 
</P>
<P>
 Reprise  
</P>
<P>
 * * * 
</P>
<P>
 Jarreau on recordings and Jarreau in performance have always been two distinct 
experiences. Producer Marcus Miller has finally solved the problem by capturing 
much of the singer's high-voltage stage spontaneity on this in-studio live 
production. 
</P>
<P>
 Jarreau's most appealing quality is his capacity to find utterly unique 
interpretations in well-known material -- in this case, a funk-rocking reading 
of "Summertime"; personalized, even quirky renderings of "Your Song" and "Try a 
Little Tenderness," and a new slant on "My Favorite Things" (in a duet with 
opera singer Kathleen Battle). 
</P>
<P>
 Jarreau may not fit the traditional mold, but his persistent musical probing 
and unerring sense of swing represent a fascinating model of contemporary jazz 
vocalizing. 
</P>
<P>
 Albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three stars 
(good, recommended), four stars (excellent). DON HECKMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
