<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEONARD FEATHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * Turtle Island String Quartet, "Who Do We Think We Are?," Windham 
Hill.Continuing to blend the best of two worlds, the TISQ here brings together 
its own daringly different interpretations of works by Parker, Monk, Victor 
Feldman and McCoy Tyner, along with a couple of in-house originals. The 
furthest-out cut is an experimental treatment of Jimi Hendrix's "Gypsy Eyes." 
Tyner's "Blues on the Corner" is the strongest jazz track and "You've Changed," 
with an expendable vocal by Vicki Randle, the weakest. David Balakrishnan, as 
always, was a key figure in the writing of a generally inspiring set. 
</P>
<P>
 Albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three stars 
(good, recommended), four stars (excellent). LEONARD FEATHER 
</P>
