</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIXED MEDIA: CRANBERRIES' SASS: WINNING LIVE VIDEO; ***; THE CRANBERRIES, "THE 
CRANBERRIES LIVE"( POLYGRAM HOME VIDEO ) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBERT HILBURN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Because this Irish band has sold more than 1 million albums without checking 
in with a high-profile U.S. tour, this 65-minute video gives most pop fans 
their first chance to see how the quartet handles itself live. 
</P>
<P>
 Is the band, led by singer Dolores O'Riordan, as seductive and smart as 
suggested by the best moments of that debut album -- "Everybody Else Is Doing 
It, So Why Can't We?" -- or is it a one-hit wonder? 
</P>
<P>
 Based on the group's performance, which was taped in January in London and 
includes seven songs not on the album, the Cranberries are indeed a promising 
young band. The quartet balances the accessibility and craft of such 
radio-friendly singles as "Linger" and "Dream" with a budding vision and 
passion that give the depth required for longevity. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Riordan's vocals, frequently brightened by an aggressive Celtic coloring, 
move between sweet innocence and alarming intensity as she explores various 
emotional contours of contemporary relationships. 
</P>
<P>
 Items are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three stars 
(good) and four stars (excellent). ROBERT HILBURN 
</P>
</TEXT>
