<P>
 *** Various artists, "DGC Rarities Vol. 1," DGC/Geffen. Is a previously 
unreleased Nirvana demo worth even the budget price of this collection? When 
that track is "Pay to Play," a 1990 punk-fury explosion that evolved into "Stay 
Away," the answer is yes.But wait, there's more: Hole's intriguing, U.K.-only 
single "Beautiful Son" and lesser but still worth-collecting efforts from Beck, 
Sonic Youth and Counting Crows make this 14-track anthology a good value. 
