<P>
BRIEFLY; DANCE: PAIR PLACE SECOND IN COUNTRY-WESTERN FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The twang of steel guitars and the thump of cowboy boots filled the air as 
couples competed Wednesday in the regional finals of a country-Western dancing 
competition at a Santa Monica nightclub. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina del Rey residents Armando Arbaca and Christine Iannone scored highest 
of all local couples but were edged from first place by Ronnie DeBennadetta and 
Carrie Dawn Hoover of Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners received $1,500 and will compete for the $10,000 prize in the 
national finals of the Marlboro Dance Showdown, to be held Dec. 7 in Arlington, 
Tex. Iannone and Arbaca got $1,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The competition at the Denim & Diamonds nightclub included the traditional 
two-step, the country-Western swing and a line dance called the "tush-push." 
Competitors were judged on precision, accuracy of dance step, showmanship and 
sportsmanship. 
</P>
