<P>
SALTWATER SHELTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUG CONNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Olympic Coast National Marine Sanctuary, a 135-mile stretch of Pacific 
Ocean along Washington's brooding Olympic Peninsula, is being dedicated this 
weekend. The underwater sanctuary, the first in the Pacific Northwest, will now 
be off-limits to oil and gas exploration and low-flying aircraft. The sanctuary 
runs parallel to an Olympic National Park wilderness area that draws 500,000 
visitors annually to hike, camp or fish. DOUG CONNER 
