<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGRY AT PICTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I couldn't help but feel disgusted and shocked by your "My Best Shot" of the 
painted elephant on parade in Jaipur, India (June 5). I am sure much of your 
intelligent and thinking readership would feel as I do: that your choice of 
such a picture represents an irresponsible and ignorant attitude on the part of 
The Los Angeles Times regarding appropriate and humane treatment of animals. 
</P>
<P>
 An animal is beautiful as nature created it, in its own environment, not 
slathered with paint all over its skin and paraded about on the hot city 
streets.  
</P>
<P>
 Let's grow up, and start teaching our children to respect the environment and 
all living beings with whom we share our world.  
</P>
<P>
 SUSAN K. OLENICK 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
