<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA 1994; SPOTLIGHT; STOIC SWEDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Swedish Coach Tommy Svensson wanted to do something for his 80-year-old 
father, Stig, who has worked for a Swedish club team for 45 years. 
</P>
<P>
 So he invited Stig to Southern California for the semifinal game against 
Brazil and Saturday's third-place game against Bulgaria. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a very emotional moment, a great moment for my father," Tommy Svensson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 What did they say to one another? 
</P>
<P>
 "We didn't say anything," Tommy Svensson said. LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
