<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA 1994; SPOTLIGHT; MUST HAVE BEEN AFTER 6 P.M. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Before today's kickoff, Chris Wentzel, Don Balch and Jeff McVey of the Wings 
Skydiving Teams will parachute into the Rose Bowl as a finale to the World 
Cup's closing ceremony. 
</P>
<P>
 Balch, from Hemet, and McVey, from Taft, will carry the Italian and Brazilian 
flags, respectively, and Wentzel, from North Hollywood, will land last, 
carrying the game ball. 
</P>
<P>
 Meeting a FIFA referee will be a piece of cake after a recent jump. 
</P>
<P>
 The three once dropped into ceremonies dressed as Alexis Carrington, the 
haughty, naughty Joan Collins character from television's "Dynasty." 
</P>
<P>
 For that jump, they wore evening gowns and were met by Collins. MATT WHITE 
</P>
</TEXT>
