<P>
WORLD CUP USA 1994; SPOTLIGHT; . . .CHECK THIS OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO CALAZANS, O Globo in Rio de Janeiro 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "If he had a little more understanding of soccer and of life, Romario would 
have more respect for Brazil's football idols, among them, of course, Zico 
(whom Romario criticized as having 'done nothing' for Brazil in Cups past). 
</P>
<P>
 "Brazil drew the second-largest crowds after the Americans in this Cup. . . . 
This prestige of Brazilian soccer is not due to Romario, though he might 
imagine it in his megalomania, but due to generations and generations of 
players whose names need no repeating because of their registered place in 
history -- and who built up the eternity of our soccer." FERNANDO CALAZANS, O 
Globo in Rio de Janeiro 
</P>
