<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALSA BEATS FT. LAUDERDALE IN SHOOTOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Littman had three consecutive saves in the shootout to help the Salsa 
beat host Ft. Lauderdale in an American Professional Soccer League game 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The score was tied, 0-0, after overtime and the Salsa won the shootout, 2-1, 
to be credited with a 1-0 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Wright and Jose Vasquez scored in the shootout for the Salsa (2-2), which 
has won two in a row. Alex Sanchez scored for Ft. Lauderdale (1-1), but Littman 
then made three consecutive saves. 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Kofe took the final shot for the Strikers but his attempt sailed high over 
the net. 
</P>
<P>
 The Salsa lost their first two games, then Littman took over in goal and the 
Salsa beat Houston, 3-0, Thursday. Littman had five saves Saturday before the 
shootout. 
</P>
<P>
 The Salsa meets Seattle on July 24 at Cal State Fullerton in its home opener. 
</P>
</TEXT>
