<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICAN LEGION BASEBALL ROUNDUP; WOODLAND HILLS EAST COMES BACK FROM EIGHT-RUN 
DEFICIT, 12-11 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Woodland Hills East rallied from eight runs down to upset Woodland Hills West, 
12-11, in a District 20 American Legion baseball game Saturday at El Camino 
Real High. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills East capped its rally in the eighth inning when David Helman's 
opposite-field single scored Mike Ross. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills East trailed, 8-0, in the fifth inning but scored five runs in 
the fifth and five more in the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 Stanford-bound Jon Schaeffer had four hits and three runs batted in while 
teammate Jacob Young added three doubles for Woodland Hills East (7-12). 
</P>
<P>
 Billy Burnette led Woodland Hills West (14-6) with a grand slam and six RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 In other District 20 games: 
</P>
<P>
 West Hills 11, Granada Hills East 6 -- Brandon Gray pitched a complete game in 
his first Legion start and also drove in four runs as West Hills (11-8) kept 
its playoff hopes alive. 
</P>
<P>
 Gray struck out five and walked eight for West Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Christian Bartlett had a home run, a double and three RBIs for Granada Hills 
East (8-12). 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys South 15, Sunland Tujunga 4 -- David Corleto collected three hits and 
three RBIs, and Aaron Amitin added a three-run double during an eight-run 
fourth inning that powered Van Nuys South to the lopsided victory at Tujunga 
Field. 
</P>
<P>
 Walter Rios (3-0) scattered four hits over seven innings for Van Nuys South. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Spielman hit a three-run home run in the sixth inning for Sunland Tujunga 
(9-11). 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley South 9, Palmdale 2 -- Chris Tapia banged out three doubles in 
Antelope Valley South's victory at Antelope Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley South (17-3) collected 15 hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys East 6, Verdugo Hills 5 -- Francisco Dongo went three for four, 
including a double in the fourth inning that drove in the winning runs for Van 
Nuys East in the first of two games. 
</P>
<P>
 Justin Bunch and Eddie Romero each added two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys East 20, Las Virgenes 6 -- Bunch led the way for with three hits and 
three RBIs, while Romero added two hits with two RBIs as Van Nuys East trounced 
Las Virgenes (12-8) for its second victory of the day. 
</P>
<P>
 Five players had two RBIs for Van Nuys East (14-4-1). Andy Lutz earned his 
second victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Las Virgenes 6, Encino Crespi 4 -- Sam Rutherford and Billy Hoover hit triples 
as Las Virgenes scored three runs in the eighth inning to pull out the victory 
at Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Melucci and Kevin Sass each had three hits for Las Virgenes (11-8). 
</P>
<P>
 In District 16 games: 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake Royal 4-5, Santa Barbara 3-3 -- Brent Egan scored the winning run in 
the bottom of the seventh in the first game when Santa Barbara failed to turn a 
double play that would have ended the inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Fernandez went two for three for Westlake Royal in the opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake Royal (24-1) held off a rally by Santa Barbara (8-10) in the seventh 
inning of the second game to get a sweep at Moorpark College. 
</P>
