<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPLASH LOSES TO SIDEKICKS IN DALLAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Splash, which Friday beat the second-best team in the Eastern Division, 
didn't fair as well against first-place Dallas on Saturday at Reunion Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sidekicks scored the game's first four goals on their way to a 9-6 victory 
before 7,408 fans.Dallas leads its division with a 10-2 record. 
</P>
<P>
 The Splash (9-4) was coming off a 9-6 victory over Monterrey at home Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 David Doyle and Eric Dade scored two goals each in the first half as Dallas 
took a 4-0 lead into halftime. Each finished with three goals and Tatu added 
two more for the Sidekicks. 
</P>
<P>
 Dade scored with 3 minutes 52 seconds left, but Dallas went ahead 9-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Raffaele Ruotolo and Dale Ervine each scored twice for the Splash, which plays 
host to the Washington Warthogs on Tuesday night at The Pond of Anaheim. 
</P>
