<P>
2 LOCAL PLAYERS PASS UP SHRINE ALL-STAR GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The North-South Shrine All-Star Football Game again will be played without any 
representatives from the Central Los Angeles area. 
</P>
<P>
 Fremont quarterback William Yates turned down the Shrine invitation in order 
to attend the Down Under Bowl, which will be played in Australia and New 
Zealand. Dennis Fomond, Crenshaw linebacker-fullback, withdrew his name because 
he had to report to practice at Cal. 
</P>
<P>
 Last season, Dorsey receiver Antonio Carrion was removed from the South team 
because he violated curfew during the practice week. 
</P>
<P>
 The 43rd annual game matches all-stars from Northern California against the 
best from Southern California on Saturday at Cerritos College. 
</P>
