<HEADLINE>
<P>
SYLMAR MAN, 32, STABBED TO DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 32-year-old man was stabbed to death in Pacoima early Sunday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 David Ramirez of Sylmar was found just after midnight by police officers 
answering a call in the 9500 block of Cranford Avenue, Los Angeles Police Sgt. 
David Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ramirez was taken to Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills, where he 
died, Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said neither a suspect nor a weapon has been found. 
</P>
</TEXT>
