<P>
JUVENILE ARRESTED IN STABBING DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 20-year-old man was stabbed to death and police have arrested a juvenile on 
suspicion of murder, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodney Corwin Ferguson, an Anaheim resident, was stabbed once Friday night and 
died at UCI Medical Center in Orange, Anaheim Police Sgt. Craig Hunter said. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident occurred at 11:40 p.m. in the 2100 block of West Dogwood Avenue, 
Hunter said. Officers responded to a report of a stabbing and found Ferguson. 
After interviewing witnesses, police arrested the suspect near Onondaga and 
Glen avenues. No additional information was available about the suspect. 
