<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; DODGERS; WORRELL STOPS TALKING AFTER QUESTIONING 
LASORDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Todd Worrell -- who sometimes offers his opinion about how Manager Tom Lasorda 
uses him and the other relievers -- has refused to talk with reporters the last 
couple of days and said that while he is not angry, he doesn't want to talk 
anymore. Worrell did not give a reason, but his comments during the last home 
stand, when he questioned Lasorda's use of the bullpen, were not received well 
by Lasorda and, apparently, Executive Vice President Fred Claire. 
</P>
<P>
 Claire said he hadn't talked to Worrell about his recent comments, but offered 
a strong opinion about complaining to the media: "If a player has something to 
say, he ought to address it directly. We have a manager, a pitching coach and a 
player. They can all communicate together." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Minor league report: Darren Dreifort, sidelined because of a strained right 
shoulder, is improved and is expected to throw off the mound today. . . . Chan 
Ho Park, who sat out a start because of stiffness in his back, is back in the 
rotation. Claire said he is pleased with the progress of both since they were 
sent to double-A San Antonio. Claire said Park is utilizing his fastball more 
and, though his walks are still high, is making progress. MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
