<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Remember to keep the mower blades high -- 2 to 2 1/2 inches tall -- to give 
the lawn enough foliage to produce food. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mulch heavily around the base of rose bushes and follow a regular watering 
program. Roses love deep, thorough waterings. 
</P>
<P>
 * For interest in foliage color and texture, look up coleus, dusty miller, 
creeping charlie or parrots beak the next time you're in the nursery. 
</P>
<P>
 * Trim off old flowers on summer annuals to prolong blooming. 
</P>
<P>
 * Plant a kitchen plot of herbs. Many of them are perennial. 
</P>
</TEXT>
