<P>
 * Resident's top recommendations: How to improve transportation. (Accepted up 
to two replies) 
</P>
<P>
 Reduce crime: 16% 
</P>
<P>
 Tougher law enforcement: 16% 
</P>
<P>
 Improve the economy: 15% 
</P>
<P>
 More police: 10% 
</P>
<P>
 Community centers with activities for children and adults: 6% 
</P>
<P>
 Crack down on illegal immigrants: 6% 
</P>
<P>
 More programs for children: 6% * Who's most responsible for making L.A. more 
livable? Family: 31% 
</P>
<P>
 Individual: 20% 
</P>
<P>
 Government: 20% 
</P>
<P>
 Business: 5% 
</P>
<P>
 Schools: 4% 
</P>
<P>
 Religious institutions: 3% 
</P>
<P>
 All equally: 15% 
</P>
<P>
 * Would you spend a few hours every few months volunteering to improve 
transportation? 
</P>
<P>
 Yes: 62% 
</P>
<P>
 No: 35% 
</P>
<P>
 Don't know: 3% * Which one of these ideas do you think would be most 
effective? 
</P>
<P>
 Turn storefronts, lots into community centers and parks: 22% 
</P>
<P>
 Create teen-age sports corps: 21% 
</P>
<P>
 Transport children to cultural events: 15% 
</P>
<P>
 Renew Downtown L.A. neighborhoods: 13% 
</P>
<P>
 Have "all-ethnic" days: 12% 
</P>
<P>
 Show short films about communities: 4% 
</P>
<P>
 Coin-operated exercise machines: 1% 
</P>
<P>
 Other/None: 8% 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Numbers may not add up to 100% because some responses are not shown. 
</P>
